findings.title: Unprotected functions
findings.description: Some functions lack access modifiers or have weak access control, allowing unauthorized users to manipulate contract parameters.

findings.title: Reentrancy vulnerabilities
findings.description: The use of low-level calls and transfers without proper reentrancy protection may lead to potential attacks.

findings.title: Unvalidated user input
findings.description: The contracts do not sufficiently validate user input, which can cause unexpected behavior or exploits.

findings.title: Poorly implemented tokenomics
findings.description: The token's economics seem unclear, with unclear consequences for investors and users.

findings.title: Lack of testing and auditing
findings.description: The contracts appear to lack thorough testing and security audits, increasing the risk of undetected vulnerabilities.

findings.title: Expected pragma, import directive or contract/interface/library definition
findings.description: Low severity issue that may or may not create any functional vulnerability

findings.title: Authorization through tx.origin
findings.description: Low severity issue that may or may not create any functional vulnerability
